Scalapay
”), in its capacity as personal data controller, respects your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal data.
This privacy policy (hereinafter, the “
Privacy Policy
”) illustrates the reasons, the methods for collection, management, and protection of the personal data of data subjects who use Scalapay’s services.
Scalapay is committed to processing your data in compliance with the General Data Protection Regulation (Regulation  (EU) 2016/679), better known as the “
GDPR
”, and with any other privacy law applicable. In particular, the personal data processing operations carried out by Scalapay shall be based on principles of lawfulness, fairness, transparency, limitation of purpose and retention, data minimization, accuracy, integrity, and
  confidentiality.
PURPOSE OF THIS PRIVACY POLICY
This Privacy Policy is drawn up in line with Articles 13 and 14 of the GDPR, and its purpose is to provide you information on the methods by which Scalapay processes your personal data, collected when you use our website and our app, including all the data you may provide to use our
  services and to receive information on any news (for instance, when you register to our newsletter, when you interact with our customer assistance team, or when you take part in a promotion or survey).
Specifically, should you decide to use the option of deferred payment in consecutive monthly instalments through Scalapay's information technology infrastructure, you, as a consumer (the "
Consumer
"), will enter into an agreement (the "
Agreement
") with a merchant engaged in the business of selling or providing products and services (hereinafter "
Merchant
").
It’s important that you read this Privacy Policy, and any other information we may provide to you to supplement, update, or further explain the information regarding the collection and processing of your personal data. We will endeavour to coordinate these communications so as to
  provide at all times a clear picture of the conditions applied to the processing of your personal data in the most transparent and easily accessible way possible.
