WHAT HAPPENS IF YOU DON’T PROVIDE YOUR PERSONAL DATA
In some cases, we need to collect your personal data in order to comply with the law or on the basis of the terms and conditions of the Agreement we have in place with you or which we are in the process of stipulating with you (for example, to provide you goods or services). In these cases,
  failure to provide your personal data may make it impossible for Scalapay to provide its services to you.
Should you decline to provide your consent to the processing of your personal data for Scalapay's additional marketing purposes, this will not have any consequences, except that you will not receive any marketing or promotional/advertising communications regarding Scalapay's
  services or products.
INTERNATIONAL TRANSFERS OF DATA
Some of the external third-parties who provide services to us are headquartered outside the European Economic Area (“
EEA
”), and therefore the processing of your personal data may entail a data transfer outside the EEA. Every time we transfer your personal data outside the EEA, we ensure an level of protection that is comparable to the one provided within the European Union, making sure that at least
  one of the following guarantees is implemented:
Adequacy decisions: when the personal data is transferred to Countries which the European Commission deemed capable of offering an adequate level of personal data protection;
Standard Contractual Clauses: in the absence of adequacy decisions, we will adopt the standard contractual clauses approved by the European Commission, which are aimed at guaranteeing the same level of personal data protection that is offered within the EU.
WHO CAN WE SHARE YOUR PERSONAL DATA WITH?
Within Scalapay's organisation, your data may be processed by the members of staff of the competent offices for the performance of single processing operations.
In addition, in order to provide our services or for the additional purposes you have consented to, we may share your personal data with the following categories of recipients, for the purposes listed below, in compliance with the principles of data minimisation and purpose limitation,
  putting in place appropriate security measures. The exact identification of the parties to whom your personal data shall be communicated will depend on the services you will use. These parties will have access to the personal data necessary to carry out the following tasks (and may not use
  them for other purposes), and will be under obligation to process data in compliance with the applicable laws. We will adopt every reasonable contractual, legal, technical, and organisational measure to guarantee that your personal data will be processed with an adequate level of protection.
  In particular, in order to provide our services, the categories of parties to whom your data will be communicated, based on and within the limits of the purposes pursued, are:
Service providers and sub-contractors: we may share your personal data with the providers and subcontractors whose services we use to provide our services. The service providers and subcontractors are companies authorised to only process the personal data they receive from Scalapay.
    Examples of said suppliers and subcontractors include software and data storage providers, payment processing providers, and company advisers.
On-line and physical shops: Scalapay may communicate your personal data to the on-line shop you visit or at which premises you make a purchase. This is done so that the shop can process and manage your purchase and your dealings with the shop, send you the goods you purchase, manage any
    disputes, and prevent fraud. The personal data communicated to a shop shall be subject to the policies and methods contained in the privacy policy adopted by said shop.
Payment Service Providers (“
PSP
”): PSPs allow electronic payments through a vast range of payment methods, including credit cards, bank transactions such as direct debit, etc.
Know-Your Customer (“
KYC
”) and Anti-Money Laundering (“
ALM
”) Agencies: Within the scope of
M
erchant “onboarding” activities, we conduct checks on the identity of the company and its beneficial owner.
Credit Recovery Agencies: Scalapay may need to share your data at the time of making a sale or when it outsources the collection of unpaid and overdue payments to third parties, such as debt collection companies.
FOR HOW LONG SHALL WE USE YOUR DATA?
We will retain your personal data only for the time necessary to fulfil the purposes for which we collected them, including the purpose of complying with any legal, book-keeping, or reporting requirement or obligation. To determine the appropriate period of time to retain your personal
  data, we take into consideration the quantity, nature, and sensitivity of your personal data, the potential risk of damages arising out of the unauthorised use or disclosure of personal data, the purposes for which we process personal data and whether or not we can attain such purposes in
  other ways, and the applicable legal requirements. You can find more information on data retention periods in the table provided in paragraph 4 above.
AUTOMATED DECISION-MAKING PROCESS
Scalapay uses automated decision-making systems which may affect your order. For more information, we invite you to read the following.
We use computer systems to approve the requests to use the services that Scalapay offers its clients. In particular, when a client selects the service offered by Scalapay, we use an automated system that takes into account signs of fraud/risk to assess whether or not our service can be
  used, and, where possible, the user’s browsing history on the platform.
The following are the potential impacts the above process may have on you: clients may be denied the possibility to use our service.
You have the right to object to this decision, express your point of view, or request an explanation for the above decision. Please contact us if you need more information or if you have any questions on the automated processing of data.
HOW DO WE PROTECT YOUR PERSONAL DATA?
We limit the quantity of data, collecting only those that are necessary for the purpose and for the time required to achieve it. We limit, protect, and monitor all of our computer resources in order to prevent any access, damage, loss, or destruction, whether physical or electronic, or any
  non-authorised access, both physical or electronic.
YOUR RIGHTS
We remind you that you may exercise your rights concerning personal data, as provided for under data protection law. These rights are briefly outlined below.
